{
  "stem": "10588.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Jewish people would be tailors and, you know, different kinds of tradesmen.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They would trade and sell and buy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we used to buy live chickens and, you know, duck and, and geese-- whatever.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we've-- what was also different than here is that, here, you want a meat that it shouldn't be fat.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There, you used to blow away the fat, as I remember like today-- see if it's fat.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it should be fat.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And you know, when the mother went to the butcher, to the kosher butcher, give me a fat piece of meat, you know?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we would buy the, the chickens there and then take them to the ritual slaughterer, which was there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one time my mother asked me to go to the ritual slaughter, to [SPEAKING YIDDISH], which means 'to slaughter the chicken.' And I don't know why she said it.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She said, don't tell the chicken that it's going to be killed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's [HEBREW], which means-- in Hebrew, it's a sin.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You're not allowed to tell any-- you know, like, you have to-- don't inflict pain on the, on the chicken.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was thinking, the chicken will understand my language?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Seemed to me very funny, you know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And also, in connection with the livestock buying from, from the peasants, is my parents used to-- in Poland, a girl needed a dowry.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So, since you were little, if you had daughters, you started to make the trousseau for the dowry and everything.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I remember, as today, my mother and grandmother sometimes used to sit, and they plucked the, the chicken, or-- so the chicken feathers they always thew away.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But when it was a geese or a duck, the down, they would, they would save.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
